The paper introduces a new method for learning knowledge graph embeddings using deep neural models, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bi-Directional LSTMs also suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database (cs.DB), and the tasks of link prediction and triple classification, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
